#: ../../W/wall.rst:19
msgid ""
"[Unix, from ‘write all’] v. To send a message to everyone currently logged "
"in, esp. with the :manpage:`wall(8)` utility."
msgstr ""
"[Unix, ‘write all’から] 動詞。現在ログインしている全員に、特に\\ :manpage:`wall(8)`\\ "
"ユーティリティを使ってメッセージを送ること。"

#: ../../W/wall.rst:22
msgid ""
"It is said that sense 1 came from the idiom ‘like talking to a blank wall’. "
"It was originally used in situations where, after you had carefully answered"
" a question, the questioner stared at you blankly, clearly having understood"
" nothing that was explained. You would then throw out a \"Hello, wall?\" to "
"elicit some sort of response from the questioner. Later, confused "
"questioners began voicing \"Wall?\" themselves."
msgstr ""
"語義1は‘like talking to a blank "
"wall(のっぺりした壁に話しかけているよう)’というイディオムから来たと言われている。それは元々、あなたが丁寧に質問に答えた後、質問者が何も理解しなかったことが明らかなまま、ぽかんとあなたを見つめる状況で使われた。すると、あなたは質問者から何らかの反応を引き出すために\"Hello,"
" wall?\"と投げかけるのだった。後には、混乱した質問者が自ら\"Wall?\"と声に出すようになった。"
